Subject: Hope for /\/\irageNet
From: Mark Hoover (1:275/103)

Dear Editor,

After the local RC put an end to my mass mailing campaign, I
have had to find another way to ask sysops to join a new network
that I'm trying to expand. I asked him for an alternative
suggestion and he said to try placing an item in FidoNews.

I'm not really enthusiastic about this approach because I'm not
to sure about how many people actually read the thing. I know a
lot of them down here in Net 285 just delete it when the file
appears. But, I'm willing to try this alternative since I'm not
left with much of a choice anymore.

If you could please give me some guidelines for posting an
article I'd appreciate it. If you'd like to see our welcome
packet for yourself you can Freq it from my system as MIRAGE.

Mark Hoover
The InnerSpace BBS, 1:275/103
/\/\irageNet Coordinator
Via 1:275/85@fidonet @19951109.232632 FrontDoor 2.12.SW

Editors note:

The specs for an article are quite simple. ASCII text only,
do not go beyond 72 characters per line, and an "*" in the first
character of a line is reserved for the title. Sending it as a
file makes it easier for us, but we will pull the article out of
a message if it comes in that way.

